## üß† Lessons Learned

### üîπ Custom Events
Socket.io allows developers to define custom events easily.

**Client (React):**
```javascript
import { io } from "socket.io-client";
const socket = io("[url where to connect]");
socket.emit("hello", data);
```

**Server (Node.js):**
```javascript
import { Server } from "socket.io";
const io = new Server(PORT);

io.on("connection", (socket) => {
  socket.on("hello", (data) => {
    // process the data
  });
});
```

### üîπ Rooms
Socket.io supports rooms for more granular message broadcasting.

**Join a Room:**
```javascript
socket.join(roomID);
```

**Leave a Room:**
```javascript
socket.leave(roomID);
```
_üí° Place these inside event listeners (e.g., inside `socket.on(...)`)._

### üîπ Emitting to Rooms

You can emit events to specific rooms:
```javascript
// To sender only
socket.emit('event_here', data.message);

// To all clients including sender
io.emit('event_here', data.message);

// To all clients except sender
socket.broadcast.emit('event_here', data.message);

// To all in room except sender
socket.broadcast.to(data.room).emit('event_here', data.message);

// To all in room including sender
io.in(data.room).emit('event_here', data.message);

// To sender if in room
socket.to(room).emit('event_here', data.message);

// To all in namespace
io.of('myNamespace').emit('event_here', data.message);

// To specific socket ID
socket.broadcast.to(socketid).emit('event_here', data.message);
```

